                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6212/26</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Administrator of the National Recovery Administration</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-23">January 23,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Replying to yours of January 12th,
                    I have no suggestions to make about the circular of the League for the Defense
                    of Jewish Rights because regardless of what they may say about the Swastika we
                    are anxious to have people patronize the Blue Eagle.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hugh S. Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
